<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4940&amp;p=44126#p44126"><![CDATA[
Any idea how the Zelda Oracle games know if they're running on GBA?  A GBA game can detect NDS by using the bios checksum software interrupt, but the Gameboy/GBC doesn't have software interrupts.  Maybe they added a new IO area to the GBC hardware inside the GBA just for that purpose.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3506">strat</a> — Tue Mar 10, 2009 10:25 pm</p><hr />
